snippet.textDisplay: If I were a betting man.. I'd be homeless right now. No way, could you have told me.. that on wildcard weekend, the Vikings would go into the Superdome, and beat New Orleans, in New Orleans. And not only that, but Kirk Cousins would play like Kirk Cousins.. and Drew Brees would be the one that played more like Curt Cousins. Kirk clearly outplayed Drew, didn't play scared, and made all the plays that needed to be made, to put his team in a position to win. Contrast that with Drew (though he made some good plays also), who did the opposite. Threw into double coverage on the interception (that lead to a Vikings td right before half), and casually held the ball in his surgically repaired hand, while being pressured by big stud Danielle Hunter before fumbling.. when you just got in scoring position, with just under 5 minutes to go in the game. BTW, Drew also got outplayed by his backup gadget specialist Taysom Hill as well. Then Kirk makes the two big throws in OT, that wins the game for the Vikings, in the Superdome?! Man. You cannot write this stuff anymore crazily. Who dat?! Who dat?! Who dat say they gonna beat dem' Saints?! The Vikings dat's who! You like that!
